20/05/2005
BUDAPEST, Hungary -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano paid a one-day visit to Hungary on Thursday (19 May), meeting with his Hungarian counterpart, Ferenc Gyurcsany. The two officials discussed bilateral ties and focused on economic co-operation possibilities. Gyurcsany pledged full support for Albania's EU integration and expressed readiness to back any initiatives aimed at accelerating the regional integration. 
Also Thursday, Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic and his Albanian counterpart, Kastriot Islami, held talks in Belgrade. Tirana supports the dialogue between Belgrade and Pristina, and feels the countries of the region should also give their input into solving the Kosovo problem, Islami said after the meeting. (Albanian News - 20/05/05; Danas, Tanjug - 19/05/05) 
